[30;1m1635 | [0m[35m	# command.[0m
[30;1m1636 | [0m[35m	LC_ALL=C; find $(srcdir)/[a-zA-Z]* '(' -name '*.fdc' -o -name '*~' \[0m
[30;1m1637 | [0m[35m				     -o -name '[@,#]*' -o -name '*.old' \[0m
[30;1m1638 | [0m[35m				     -o -name '*.orig' -o -name '*.rej' \[0m
[30;1m1639 | [0m[35m				     -o -name '*.bak' ')' \[0m

[30;1m45 | [0m[35m<command>Odfuserfield</command> is a program that will list or change[0m
[30;1m46 | [0m[35mthe user variable declarations in an OpenDocument file.[0m
[30;1m47 | [0m[35mThere are two kinds of variables in OpenDocument. Simple variables can[0m
[30;1m48 | [0m[35mtake different values at different positions, throughout a document.[0m
[30;1m49 | [0m[35mUser variables have the same value throughout a document. Due to the latter's[0m
[30;1m50 | [0m[35mglobal nature it is safe to change them with an external application.[0m
